-- Peru Stocks: Candente, Casa Grande, Panoro, Southern
-- B y   A l e x   E m e r y
-- 2012-07-18T20:41:36Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-07-18/peru-stocks-candente-casa-grande-panoro-southern.html
The following companies had unusual
price changes in  Peru  trading. Stock symbols are in parentheses,
and share prices are as of the close of trade in  Lima .  The  Lima General Index (IGBVL)  rose 0.3 percent to 20,088.64. The
MSCI All Peru Capped Index climbed 0.2 percent to 2,699.54.  Casa Grande (CASAGRC1)  (CASAGRC1 PE), Peru’s largest sugar producer
and a unit of Gloria SA, rose 2.4 percent to 13.11 soles after
sugar gained for a fourth day in  New York , said  Francisco Miranda , an analyst at Lima-based investment fund NC&F
Inversiones SA.  Candente Copper Corp. (DNT)  , a Canadian exploration
company, climbed 1.9 percent to 54 cents after copper advanced
in New York.  Southern Copper Corp. (SCCO)  , Peru’s biggest copper
producer, gained 1.6 percent to $32.  Panoro Minerals Ltd. (PML)  , a Canadian copper and gold
exploration company, advanced 1.6 percent to 64 cents.  Maple Energy Plc (MPLE)  , the oil and natural gas
producer with operations in Peru, rose 1 percent to $1.04 after
crude advanced for a sixth session in New York.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Alex Emery in Lima at 
 aemery1@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
